---
source: crates/agent-burn-cli/src/tests.rs
expression: help_text()
---
USAGE:
  agent-burn [summary] [RANGE] <OPTIONS>
  agent-burn harness <codex|claude> <OPTIONS>

COMMANDS:
  summary                    Compare API-equivalent agent usage with subscription value
  harness                    Inspect one subscription harness with live limits and value

For more info, run any command with the `--help` flag:
  agent-burn summary --help
  agent-burn harness --help

OPTIONS:
  -j, --json                           Output in JSON format (default: false)
  -s, --since <since>                  Filter from date (YYYY-MM-DD or YYYYMMDD)
  -u, --until <until>                  Filter until date (inclusive)
  -z, --timezone <timezone>            Timezone for date grouping (IANA) (default: system timezone)
  -m, --mode <mode>                    Cost calculation mode (default: auto, choices: auto | calculate | display)
  -o, --order <order>                  Sort order for loaded usage rows (default: asc, choices: asc | desc)
  -b, --breakdown                      Include per-model cost breakdowns (default: false)
  -O, --offline                        Use cached pricing and skip live subscription-limit calls (default: false)
  --no-offline                         Allow live pricing and subscription-limit calls
  --compact                            Force compact table layout for narrow terminals (default: false)
  --single-thread                      Disable parallel JSONL file loading (default: false)
  --no-cost                            Hide cost information in table and JSON output (default: false)
  --color                              Enable colored output. FORCE_COLOR=1 has the same effect. (default: auto)
  --no-color                           Disable colored output. NO_COLOR=1 has the same effect. (default: auto)
  --config <config>                    Path to configuration file (default: auto-discovery)
  -q, --jq <jq>                        Run a jq-style filter against JSON output
  -d, --debug                          Show pricing mismatch information for debugging (default: false)
  --debug-samples <debug-samples>      Number of sample discrepancies to show in debug output (default: 5)
  -h, --help                           Display this help message
  -v, --version                        Display this version
